definitions.explanation_en: A feminine given name, commonly used in English-speaking countries, derived from the name Jane, which itself originates from the Hebrew name Yochanan, meaning 'God is gracious'.
definitions.explanation_cn: 一个在英语国家常用的女性名字，源自名字 Jane，而 Jane 又源于希伯来语名字 Yochanan，意为‘上帝是仁慈的’。
definitions.example_en: Janet is the project manager at our new office in Seattle.
definitions.example_cn: 珍妮特是我们西雅图新办公室的项目经理。
